<exercise checkit-seed="0001" checkit-slug="LT4" checkit-title="Continuity">
    <statement>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>Determine the value of <m>b</m> to make <m>h(x)</m> continuous at <m>x=4</m>. Explain your reasoning using limits.</p>
                <p>
                    <me>
                        h(x) = \begin{cases}
                        b x + \frac{12}{5}, &amp; x \leq 4 \\
                        -x^{2} + 12 \, x - 28, &amp; x &gt; 4
                        \end{cases}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
Classify the type of discontinuity present at <m>x=-5</m> for 
the function <m>f(x)</m>. Explain your reasoning using limits. </p>
                <p>
                    <me>
                        f(x) = \begin{cases}
                        -3 \, x - 11, &amp; x &lt; -5 \\
                        9, &amp; x = -5 \\
                        -7 \, x - 31, &amp; x &gt; -5 \\
                        \end{cases}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <ol>
            <li>To make <m>h(x)</m> continuous at <m>x=4</m>, let <m>b=\frac{2}{5}</m>.</li>
                <li>
The function <m>f(x)</m> has a
removable discontinuity.
                </li>
        </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
